istration%20of%20Births%20and%20Deaths%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%20The%20Jan%20Vishwas%20(Amendment%20of%20Provisions)%20Bill%2C%20and%20the%20Government%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20(Amendment)%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20everything%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20the%20four%20new%20laws%20and%20how%20they%20will%20benefit%20the%20common%20man%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EDigital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%202023%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Data%20Protection%20Act%20aims%20to%20protect%20the%20privacy%20of%20Indian%20citizens.%20Under%20this%20law%2C%20entities%20that%20misuse%20or%20fail%20to%20safeguard%20individuals'%20digital%20data%20can%20face%20penalties%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%20250%20crore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompanies%20handling%20user%20data%20will%20be%20required%20to%20safeguard%20the%20individual's%20information%2C%20and%20instances%20of%20personal%20data%20breach%20have%20to%20be%20reported%20to%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20(DPB)%20and%20the%20user.%20According%20to%20the%20law%2C%20data%20of%20children%20can%20only%20be%20processed%20after%20consent%20from%20guardians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20private%20entities%20but%20the%20government%20is%20also%20liable%20for%20any%20data%20breach%20of%20citizens%20under%20this%20law%2C%20Union%20Minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frs-250-cr-penalty-for-every-breach-in-data-protection-bill-says-minister-4266606%5C%22%3ERajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20told%20NDTV%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20its%20core%2C%20the%20law%20basically%20focuses%20on%20the%20responsible%20processing%20of%20digital%20personal%20data%2C%20ensuring%20that%20individuals'%20rights%20are%20respected%20while%20enabling%20legitimate%20data%20usage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EGovernment%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20(Amendment)%20Bill%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20of%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20replaces%20the%20ordinance%20on%20transfers%20and%20postings%20of%20senior%20officers%20in%20the%20Delhi%20government.%20The%20law%20empowers%20the%20central%20government%20to%20control%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Delhi%20government%20by%20having%20the%20final%20say%20in%20the%20postings%20and%20transfers%20of%20bureaucrats%20and%20employees.%20It%20also%20overrules%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20that%20noted%2C%20after%20an%20eight-year%20battle%2C%20that%20the%20elected%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20government%20would%20take%20charge%20of%20the%20bureaucracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20Registration%20of%20Births%20and%20Deaths%20(Amendment)%20Bill%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20law%20will%20allow%20the%20use%20of%20a%20birth%20certificate%20as%20a%20single%20document%20for%20numerous%20purposes%20such%20as%20admission%20to%20an%20education%20institute%2C%20issuance%20of%20a%20driving%20licence%2C%20preparation%20of%20a%20voter%20list%2C%20Aadhaar%20number%2C%20registration%20of%20marriage%20or%20appointment%20to%20a%20government%20job.%20The%20law%20will%20help%20create%20a%20national%20and%20state-level%20record%20of%20registered%20births%20and%20deaths%2C%20which%20will%20eventually%20ensure%20efficient%20and%20transparent%20public%20services%20and%20social%20benefits%20through%20digital%20registration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20Jan%20Vishwas%20(Amendment%20of%20Provisions)%20Bill%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20fourth%20law%20aims%20to%20promote%20ease%20of%20business%20by%20decriminalising%20minor%20offences%20through%20amendments%20in%20183%20provisions%20of%2042%20Acts.%20The%20act%20converts%20several%20fines%20to%20penalties%2C%20meaning%20that%20punishments%20can%20be%20given%20without%20going%20to%20court.%20It%20also%20removes%20imprisonment%20as%20a%20punishment%20for%20many%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691854800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-06%2F4hlq1l6g_gavel_625x300_06_June_22.jpg%22%2C%22orig